commit.message:
Retrieve Automat's version from the installed distribution.

Automat uses setuptools-scm to derive the version from git tags, so
this keeps the version in the docs consistent with the version on
PyPI.

commit.message: Claim 3.8 support.
3.8 shouldn't fail any more.

Add support for positional only arguments

PEP 570 adds "positional only" arguments to Python, which changes the
code object constructor. This adds support for Python 3.8.

Signed-off-by: Robert-André Mauchin <zebob.m@gmail.com>
